# 1. 『STAY GOLD』

An: Alright! Now that we're all here, let's talk about our plans for the future.
Kohane: You wanted to discuss what kinds of events Vivid BAD SQUAD should be in next?
Kohane: Hehe, it's like we're a real team now!
Akito: What do you mean like a real team? We ARE a real team.
Akito: Anyways, we need to decide what sorts of events to gear up for as a group from now on.
Toya: Yeah, the BAD DOGS and Vivids have completely different styles so...
Toya: We should find something that's a good fit for everyone.
An: Yeah, I've been thinking about what would be good for us, but there are just so many choices.
Kohane: Um... Are there that many different types of events?
An: Oh, right. You've only done invitational ones before.
An: The events that are held around here broadly fall into one of two categories.
An: First, you have invitation-based ones, where a venue asks certain artists to perform.
Kohane: That's what we did as the Vivids.
Kohane: It was a little overwhelming at first, but everyone was so friendly that I forgot about being anxious really quickly.
Akito: Yeah, those events are organized among friends, so they're pretty laidback. The other event category is battles.
Kohane: B-Battles?! You fight each other?
An: Hahaha, kind of but it's pretty standard. Groups perform and compete for the audience's votes.
An: The group that gets the audience fired up the most wins. Pretty simple, right?
Toya: Competitive events are more intense...
Toya: But treating one another with respect is very important in this kind of community, so you don't need to stress.
Akito: The rules can differ based on the venue too. We can look into details after picking an event to go for.
Kohane: I see, they are different from what I've done... But they sound fun too.
An: Right? And now there's four of us, it's totally worth giving them a try.
MEIKO: Your order's ready! Two coffees and two cafes au lait.
An: Thank you so much, MEIKO!
Toya: Great aroma as always.
MEIKO: I also brought you some cookies. I'm thinking about adding them to the menu. Please, try them!
Kohane: Oh, they look yummy...! All for free... Are you really sure?
MEIKO: Oh, of course. I hope you like them.
MEIKO: So, how's your discussion going? All good?
Akito: Yeah, I think so. We're trying to decide which events to be in next.
MEIKO: Ah, I see.
Akito: Come to think of it, STAY GOLDEN is coming up. That one's a battle event, right?
An: Yeah. RUST played at the last one, and everyone went wild when they were on.
Kohane: Are they that good?
An: They're top tier! They did RAD WEEKEND together with my dad's group. All of their songs are awesome!
Kohane: Hehe, sounds like you really look up to them.
An: Hmm, I guess I do. It'd be great to sing at an event featuring them too.
An: Hey, you know what...?
An: We should enter STAY GOLDEN! How's that sound?
Kohane: What...?!
An: The best groups all participate, so it'd be a real trial by fire for us!
Akito: We could give it a go, and try to turn more heads than RUST did last time.
An: Yeah! Go big or go home!
Toya: Playing as guests at our last event was fun, but it's more satisfying to be competing.
Kohane: (They're all excited about it... But it's going to be a big challenge for me. I have zero experience with this sort of event.)
MEIKO: Are you okay, Kohane? You seem a little tense...
MEIKO: If you're worried about something, maybe I can offer some advice?
Kohane: I, umm...
Kohane: I-I'm fine! I was just lost in my thoughts for a moment.
MEIKO: Is that so? I must have misread your expression.
Kohane: Y-Yes... I'm sorry for causing a fuss over nothing!
Kohane: (I am honestly a bit anxious, but if my friends are with me... I'm sure it'll work out...!)
Kohane: (Besides, I've performed in front of an audience many times now. It can't be that much different...!)
Kohane: An! I'm going to give this event everything I've got!
An: Great! You're gonna do fine. I mean, the audience loved you at our last show!
Kohane: Right! It's still a little intimidating, but I'll try to sing just like I did then.
An: Have more confidence, girl. You're a mind-blowing singer.
Kohane: Hehe... Thanks, An!
MEIKO: Hehe. I can't wait to hear how it goes for you. I'll be rooting for you.
An: Okay, will do!
An: How about we practice today to start work on our event routine? Is everybody okay with going to the park as usual?
MEIKO: You're welcome to use the stage at my cafe, if you like.
Kohane: Are you sure you don't mind?
MEIKO: Of course. It's all yours.
An: MEIKO... Thank you so much! We'll put it to good use!
An: STAY GOLDEN's tomorrow! I hope you're pumped up!
An: Wanna do a full rehearsal?
Toya: Alright. I'll count us in.
An: Kay! Whenever you're ready, Toya.
Toya: Let's go. One, two, three, four!
An & Kohane: ♪——!
Akito & Toya: ♪——! ——! ——!
An: (The four of us sync up so well!)
Kohane: ♪!
An: (Kohane's really got a great voice...)
An: (With this much talent, it makes no sense for her to lack confidence.)
An: (Maybe she's afraid of making a mistake because she's inexperienced...?)
An: (But even if she did slip up, we'd be there to pick her back up and keep going!)
Akito: We've improved a lot. I think we're good to go.
Toya: Agreed. We've nailed everything down.
Kohane: I really like singing with you guys. I'm having so much fun, it's making my heart race!
An: I can't see us not winning STAY GOLDEN!
An: But we can't let our guard down. We can always use more practice!
Akito: Sure thing. We've set our sights not just on winning the event, but also putting on something bigger than RAD WEEKEND!
Kohane: Um... I can't help feeling anxious... Imagining all the things that could go wrong...
An: You've got nothing to worry about, Kohane.
An: In the unlikely event that something does go wrong, I'll cover for you and get you back on track, okay?
Akito: Wait, why are you saying that to her?
An: Something wrong, Akito?
Akito: Nah, forget it... Are you two...? Well, nevermind...
An: Hm...?
Kohane: Thanks, An. You can be sure that I'm going to give this show everything I have!
An: I know you will! If you ever get lost, just focus on my voice!
Kohane: Okay! Hehe. It's good to know you've got my back!
An: Haha, of course I do! We're a team!
Akito: ...
